next
  Summary: Loot Balance. Online NPCs are continuously trimmed so long-lived stalkers (story NPCs, companions, gulag survivors) never accumulate corpse-sized hoards. Per-category min/max policy lives in configs/alifebalance/ab_inventory_policy.ltx (DLTX-overridable) with explicit equipped-slot ammo ceilings, closing the equipped-ammo blind spot that the hardcoded cull table left open. Traders are skipped so their stock is untouched. Smart Pacing renamed to Smart Balance (label only, no behavior change).
  Added:
    Added: Loot Balance. Periodic scanner walks online stalkers in small batches and trims each one at most once per game-day. The population that survives is the population that hoards, so hundreds of long-lived stalkers kept driving save bloat, server-object inflation, and steady performance drag under the previous death-time approach. The scanner closes that gap. Per-category min/max ceilings loaded from configs/alifebalance/ab_inventory_policy.ltx (DLTX-overridable); anything above the max is released. Shared LTX shape with ap_trade_policy.ltx and ap_stash_policy.ltx (xlibs xinventory.load_policy). Covers equipped-slot ammo (rounds), grenades, consumables, and gear; explicit entries for ammo_slot_2_t1, ammo_slot_2_t2, ammo_slot_3_t1, ammo_slot_3_t2 close the equipped-ammo blind spot (the hardcoded cull table had no entries for these, so equipped-rifle ammo hoards passed through unbounded). Quest items, equipped gear, and untouchables (xinventory pre-filters quest / anim / blacklisted) are never touched. Traders are skipped at the scheduler level (xcreature.is_unscriptable). MCM (General -> Loot Balance) defaults: enable on, NPCs per frame 1, NPCs per cycle 20, per-NPC rescan cooldown 24 game-hours. Requires NPC corpse looting enabled. Disable "311- NPC Stop Looting Dead Bodies - DTTheGunslinger" or any equivalent NPC-loot disabler for full benefit.
    Added: configs/alifebalance/ab_inventory_policy.ltx. Per-category ceilings: rifle ammo 200 rounds, pistol ammo 64 rounds, ammo_not_equipped 0 (release on sight), grenades 3, grenade_ammo 10, medkit/bandage 20, antirad/stim/pill/food 10, drink 5, ruck weapons/outfits/helmets/artefacts/crafting/device/money/other 0.
  Changed:
    Renamed: Smart Pacing is now labelled Smart Balance in MCM, readme, and architecture. Label only, no behavior change. Internal script and config keys (ab_pacing, last_respawn_update, advances, min_minutes) unchanged.
    Changed: Smart Balance death counter credits every non-vermin death. Previously dropped story-NPC, trader, named-NPC, task-giver, companion, and task-target deaths via xsquad.is_protected.
    Changed: Loot Balance scanner enable-tooltip rewritten (eng + rus) to describe the new LTX-loaded per-category min/max policy. Old text referenced the dropped [keep_one] / [keep_items] / surplus_per_category scheme and a previous hardcoded cull table.
  Removed:
    Removed: hardcoded CULL_POLICY table in ab_loot_balance.script. Replaced by the LTX file. Backstop semantics unchanged for the categories already covered; new explicit entries for the four ammo_slot_X_tY categories close the hoarding gap on equipped ammo.
    Removed: public ab_loot_balance.evaluate_item / build_state / default_policy. Internal-only; no external callers. Per-item decision now lives inside xlibs xinventory.iterate_surplus. trim_npc(npc, opts) stays as the single public entry point.
    Removed: orphan MCM strings ui_mcm_ab_general_surplus_per_category and _desc (eng + rus). The MCM key was dropped from defaults earlier; the string table entries lingered as dead text.

1.0.2
  Summary: Crash fix on xlibs 1.7.0
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing on xlibs 1.7.0 at ab_recipe.script:141. Adopt renamed xsmart.find_smarts_spawning (was xsmart.find_smarts_with_recipe pre-1.7.0). Requires xlibs 1.7.0+.

1.0.1
  Summary: Crash fix on malformed respawn params, third-party respawn-delay compatibility
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing budget evaluation when scanning malformed or misconfigured smart terrains whose respawn_params.num condlist has no default branch.
  Compatibility:
    Skip smart terrains whose last_respawn_update is set to a future game-time by another mod. Honors third-party deferred-respawn intent instead of overriding it.

1.0.0
  First release. Advances respawn cooldowns at smart terrains where combat has produced deaths, so active regions recover faster without affecting the rest of the map.
